itemListElement.name: Private Pike Place Market Tour and Cooking Class with a Local

name: Private Pike Place Market Tour and Cooking Class with a Local
description:
Discover Pike Place market through the eyes of local who considers it her favorite market to shop! Autumn introduces you to her favorite vendors while shopping for ingredients for your Pacific Northwest cooking class.

After the market tour, join Autumn in her modest Capitol Hill apartment for a 2-hour cooking class. Autumn has a wonderful way of sharing and explaining cooking techniques that you can replicate at home. Enjoy this authentic food experience with a Culinary Institute graduate who also has a masters in gastronomy. Immerse yourself in the culture and cuisine of Seattle with this delightful local host!

review.name: Thank you Autumn!
review.reviewBody:
Thank you Autumn for the wonderful experience! We had a great time learning some new techniques under your guidance. The time was well spent!

We both really appreciated your attention to our likes and dislikes, and our input on what flavors we were partial to. We also really enjoyed your down-to-earth approach to finding flavors. This was a wonderful day, totally suitable whether we were total beginners to cooking or more experienced.

description: 2120 is an understatedly chic, independently owned and operated restaurant, serving contemporary American cuisine that uses locally sourced, and sustainable, ingredients. We're located right next to the Amazon Spheres, and only blocks from the Space Needle, in Downtown Seattle. Using only the freshest ingredients from farms in and around our local countryside, our culinary team has put together a seasonally changing menu that captures our unique culinary spirit. We're proud to feature a broad selection of wines with a focus on the Pacific Northwest. We firmly believe that what grows together goes together, and you’ll find this commitment reflected in our wine list. Our talented team behind the bar has designed an approachable, playful, and creative cocktail menu that makes an effort to tie in elements from the kitchen to the bar. We look forward to hosting you soon!

name: Skagit Valley Tulip Festival Tour
description:
The tour begins in Seattle in comfortable coaches to the scenic farmlands of the Skagit Valley, home of the largest producer of Tulip Bulbs in North America. You'll have two hours to visit beautiful tulip gardens and walk around acres of fields of tulips in the morning and then have a midday break in LaConner, Washington rated "The Most Romantic Getaway" in Washington State. During this time you can enjoy a meal at many of their highly rated restaurants or shop at the wonderful boutiques and stores. 

Finally we head back to Seattle in a comfortable coach with transport back to the Hyatt Regency in Seattle. 

All VIP garden admission fees included in price

review.name: Delightful Tulip Tour
review.reviewBody: We loved our tour of the Skagit Valley Tulips!  Our guide, Terry, was so knowledgeable, friendly and relaxed.  He took care of us by getting us to the tulip farm right when they were opening and even adding in rest area stops during our drive to and from.  It was so nice not to have to drive, worry about parking, etc.  We just got to enjoy both the tulip fields and La Conner.  We would recommend this trip to our friends and family absolutely!

review.name: Amazing Tulip Trip
review.reviewBody: Absolutely a wonderful tour, it’s been the highlight of my trip. Terry our guide was amazing, he shared his knowledge of the area and tulips with the group, which really added to the overall experience. He knew where to go and when to avoid the large crowds. So thankful for him and to get to see so many beautiful tulips and daffodils was a real treat. Highly recommend Shutter Yours and Terry as your guide, you can’t go wrong.

review.name: Birthday trip
review.reviewBody: Terry was Very friendly and knowledgeable when it came to Seattle and the tulip festival. The bus was clean and warm. He allowed plenty of time to see and do everything. I even got to see a bald eagle for the first time. And when the weather turned sour he allowed us to stay in the bus and out of the rain. I came to Seattle for my birthday and this tour really astounded me. I highly recommend this tour and will be sure to do it again next year!!

review.name: Wonderful tour of the tulips!
review.reviewBody: Highly recommend this tour. Guide Terry is very knowledgable and kind and provides great photography tips for taking pictures of the tulips. The shuttle was clean and comfortable.  Well done and well paced tour.

review.name: Definitely use this company for your tulip tour!
review.reviewBody: This is the best way to see the tulips. It's an early start but it is well worth it. Terry got us there before the crowds arrived and there was no standing in line. We got plenty of time at all of the stops and he gave us lots of good information and tips. Just an all-around great day!

review.name: Awesome! No doubts, go for it!
review.reviewBody: The tour was amazing. Along with the main tulip farm we were also given a tour of a second farm up close where we could see the working farmers. The stop at La Conner was awesome too. The food choices and artistic mind in the town are added features which made this tour memorable for me

review.name: Tulips 2022
review.reviewBody: We did this tour twice in one week, and had an amazing time on each one. We loved Terry and his team and would highly recommend this tour to anyone looking for a laid back day filled with color from the tulip fields.

review.name: Must book!
review.reviewBody: I have nothing but great things to say about this tour, tour guide and tour company! We attended the Skagit Valley Tulip Festival Tour and it was incredible. Our tour guide, Terry, was clearly very knowledgeable about Skagit Valley, the tulips and photo tips. He was so helpful throughout the day. Tour was the perfect timing. We never felt rushed throughout the day as I have on tours before. Would book again!!!

review.name: Fabulous flower display experience
review.reviewBody: The weather was optimal and the flowers were at peak blossom.  The bus ride was relaxing and the tour guide took care of all arrangements as far as tickets and directions for lunch break.

review.name: An amazing experience!
review.reviewBody: My mom and I enjoyed this tour very much. It was everything we expected to be. The tulips were incredible and absolutely breathtaking. Terry is super friendly, gave us some great tips on taking better photos.

name: Zipline Canopy Tour
description: Located on historic Kristoferson Farm on Camano Island, our canopy tour is a forest experience like nothing else! Walking between the zips, you will learn about the fascinating nature, wildlife and the rich history of the land. Then you will see an exhilarating new view as you zip between the trees! Enjoy an unforgettable time as your guides (certified to ACCT standards and first aid/CPR trained) take care of clip-ins and all the other details.

review.name: Amazing experience
review.reviewBody: We had a great time. The guides were fun and knowledgeable. An excellent adventure in a beautiful location.

review.name: THe thing I that was cool, the tour guides explained everything to us.  They took their time with everyone, it was nice.
review.reviewBody:
Enjoyed my aventure with my grandson for his birthday. It was total fun that day.
The guilds were very helpful.  THey talked me through stepping off the plathform was okay, that he would be fine. Once he did, whoa! what a thrill they had.

review.name: Marian Wall
review.reviewBody:
Canopy Tours on Camano Island was excellent! 
The office staff was professional and pleasant. The guides, Patty and Dave were great! Their attention to safety procedures was top notch. They were both very personable and made our experience that much more fun. We will definitely be coming back!

review.name: Good Times
review.reviewBody: I came for my first ever zip line experience with three friends. We had a blast! Learning a little about the forest as we hiked to the first line was interesting. Pat (Patty) and Andrew made us feel safe and added some humor to the experience. It was fun, and I would recommend it to anyone!

review.name: 45th Birthday Flying High
review.reviewBody: Thanks to our super fun guides, David and Andrew, we had a blast zipping in the beautiful NW on this amazing Canopy Tour. The zip lines were great, the special lavender cider next to a warm fire and the camaraderie were priceless! Thank you for your local stories and fun loving attitudes while keeping us safe and entertained! We had a fabulous time celebrating our son’s 45th birthday.

review.name: Look ma, i can fly!
review.reviewBody: Needed something to kickstart spring. Zipping w these guys was PERFECT!  Very professional, "safety-first" oriented, and fun. They made sure we were comfortable and that we had a blast of an adventure. definitely recommend to all, including first time zipppers; they'll take care of you!

review.name: Zipline Tour!!!
review.reviewBody: This tour was amazing! I had to reschedule the tour and Nancy was so nice about it, she understood the situation and allowed me and my two friends to switch days. I’m afraid of heights but Jenna and Dave made me feel so safe and secure and supported while zip lining. That helped a lot! They also made my friend feel special because this was a late birthday trip for her. I would 100% recommend coming here and ziplining!

review.name: Fun family adventure close to home!
review.reviewBody: My family and I had a fantastic time doing the ziplining tour. Everyone  - from Taylor in the office, to our guides, Jenna and Patrick, were fun, outgoing, and incredibly accomodating. I will DEFINITELY be back to do this again - maybe in the winter... Thank you all for a wonderful day! We really needed this!

review.name: Best experience ever!
review.reviewBody: This was a great experience that I would definitely do again. The place is amazing Staff were profesional and friendly. I recommend  this place 100%.

review.name: Super!
review.reviewBody: What a blast!  Our two staff leaders were outstanding - patient, thorough and so fun.  It was a great afternoon!

name: Pacific Northwest Peaks & Pours
description:
Pacific Northwest Peaks & Pours tour is a craft beer enthusiasts dream come true. The 8-day excursion winds its way from Seattle to Portland, Ashland and Bend, with behind-the-scenes tours and tastings as some of the countries most coveted breweries. Along the way we will experiences the iconic sites of the region and make sure you have plenty of down time to enjoy exploring on your own.

name: Northwest Wine & Rail Tour (4-night)
description: Ride the rails and take a journey to the heart of Eastern Washington and Wine Country. Enjoy the rugged Mountain views and Bavarian charms of Leavenworth. Grand vistas of the Columbia River, pioneer history, and world class wines await you in Walla Walla, Washington’s friendliest town. Sun-kissed Yakima Valley offers the largest variety of fresh grown produce in the Pacific Northwest - grapes for wine, hops for beer and fresh produce for your table. Scenic stops will offer you a taste of this region before we wind our way through the heavily wooded and volcanically formed Cascadia Range and back to beautiful Seattle.

name: Northwest Explorer with Rail (6-nights)
description: The Pacific Northwest with its unique cities, charming small towns, scenic waterways and majestic mountains is one of the most stunningly diverse regions in the world. The 7-day NW Explorer introduces you to Washington and Oregon and the Northwest lifestyle while offering two unique train rides. Enjoy the rugged Mountain views and Bavarian charms of Leavenworth. Take a journey to the rolling hills of Eastern Washington and Wine Country. World class wine awaits as you travel the pioneer trail to “Washington’s friendliest town,” Walla Walla. In Oregon, the historic Western town of Pendleton is your gateway to the Volcanoes and Waterfalls of the Columbia River Gorge. Portland Oregon, “the City of Roses,” has a style all its own.

review.name: A fantastic experience!
review.reviewBody: We traveled in May 2019 with Guy Glaeser (of Inquisitours) on this wonderful journey through the wine regions of Washington and the Columbia River Gorge. We were struck by the fantastic beauty of this part of the U.S. and how friendly the people were as we made our way across Washington and back through Oregon. The itinerary that Guy and Robin put together was excellent -- we really feel we saw the "best of the best" in this region -- and our time together included enough flexibility that we could request customizations that Guy willingly included. Guy knew all of the best wineries, and we learned so much about the landscape and history of these areas. He also had suggestions on what to see and where to eat when we were on our own. We were able to also enjoy time with Robin (and their children!), so that by the end of the week, we felt like we had been traveling with friends we had known for a long time. Guy and Robin have created a tour experience with just the right mix of structure and flexibility. We HIGHLY recommend this company!

itemListElement.name: Seattle to Victoria, BC High-Speed Passenger Ferry - ROUND TRIP

name: Seattle to Victoria, BC High-Speed Passenger Ferry - ROUND TRIP
description: Taking a trip from Seattle to Victoria, British Columbia, in Canada has never been easier, or more beautiful. Take a day trip to explore the beautiful town of Victoria on the Victoria Clipper, leaving from downtown Seattle. The high-speed Victoria Clipper will take you on a relaxing 3-hour cruise through the Puget Sound to Victoria’s Inner Harbor. This passenger-only ferry features a host of great amenities, like roomy, comfortable seats, an on-board duty-free gift shop and locally sourced food and beverage available for purchase. A U.S. passport, passport card, enhanced driver’s license or an enhanced ID card (EDL/ID) is required to cross the U.S./Canadian border.

review.name: Poor experience
review.reviewBody: Trip up to Victoria was smooth. Trip back to Vancouver was canceled day before. Terrible options provided by the Clipper and no relief for people that took a big financial hit to figure out another option. We traveled with a toddler without a car seat so we couldn’t utilize any car options. They did not provide any financial compensation outside of a refund for the one way route that was canceled.

review.name: WiFi Free Zone!?
review.reviewBody: No Wi-Fi in 2024? There's no excuse for that. Multiple providers available to solve this and the FAQ online regarding this issue is factually incorrect. Stick a Starlink panel on the roof and BAM, problem solved.

review.name: Clipper to Victoria no ac nauseous from body odor
review.reviewBody: Took my mom to Victoria for mother's day.  Trip up was fine. Seats are dated but good enough.  Windows are worn and damn near impossible to see out of. The trip back was a nightmare.  The air conditioning was broken.  It was well into the nineties and even hotter on the boat. They put some water out but ran out of ice and did not refill the water. The worst part was the body odor. It made me nauseous.  People were sweating through their clothes. The  outside deck was so crowded it was impossible to go out. They opened the upper doors for a while, this cooled the upper deck some what. The downstairs front cabin never cooled off. They didn't open the door to let any air in. When we got back to Seattle it was 84 and that was way cooler than the boat. These people could care less . Do better fsc clipper

review.name: Family Time
review.reviewBody:
The Clipper to Victoria and back was excellent the new ferry was nice and comfortable.The boarding areas were a little tight but once the team made it clear on how they were boarding and unloading us it was perfect!  NO CROWDING!! It provided pre-boarding folks room to walk through to the Ferry.

Our stay at the Coast Victoria Hotel & Marina by APA was also excellent as usual.

review.name: Seattle to Victoria for 2 overnight stays
review.reviewBody: First, my deepest appreciation to Desiree DLGuerrerro who made the arrangement for us on this Seattle/Victoria vacation package and putting up with all my emails and phone calls to dot the i's and cross the t's.  She made me feel a lot more confident that everything would roll smoothly.  I'm glad I met her the day we departed for Victoria to thank her personally, such a sweet lady.  It's always nice to put a face to the voice over the phone.  Our vacation package included 3 nights in Seattle and 2 nights in Victoria with a side trip to Butchart Gardens.   Everything went smoothly on our trip to Victoria.  We parked at their recommended parking garage which was only $10/day. Easy walking distance to the Clipper Terminal.  The Victoria Clipper was a beautiful boat with comfortable seating and onboard food service.  We did not have any issues with seating going, coming back was a little fuller, but Desiree upgraded us to priority Group 1 boarding.  You will board by groups.  Clipper Vacations arranged for us to stay at the Chateau Victoria, which is a very nice hotel within walking distance to the Clipper Terminal if you have just carry-on baggage.  Again, very pleased on how well the whole trip went.

review.name: Value for money
review.reviewBody: I took a 3 day Vacation in Victoria traveling  on the 7.30 am boat . Check-in was fairly painless , arriving in plenty of time . Even had Breakfast before boarding .Plenty of choice and reasonable priced . The trip was smooth and on time . Going through custom was a bit slow but can not blame the company . Bought the Tickets month ahead in Australia and had no hassles.

review.name: Package tour Very Pleased with this sidetrip!
review.reviewBody: We bought a 2-day/one night with tea at the Empress and tickets to the Garden. Opted for comfort class and very happy with the $20/price tag each way for the complimentary non-alcoholic beverages and snacks. Easy boarding with this option. We all did carry-on and it was a breeze. Great hotel in the package (Grand Pacific). We went on the 3:30pm ferry and returned the next day boarding at 5pm. We wanted to stay longer...Victoria is just beautiful.

review.name: Glad we did took the overnight Victoria trip
review.reviewBody: We had putting off this overnight trip to Victoria, BC, from our home in Seattle, and it's unfortunate we waited this long. Anyway, we took the Victoria Clipper from Pier 69 in Seattle and found it to be an easy and relaxing ride across the water. We even used the Clipper's hotel specials to stay at the Rialto Hotel, which was wonderful. On the Clipper, the attendants are all very cheery and pleasant and everything is explained over the loud speaker so there should be little confusion of the processes. During the summer months, the lines and waiting to get on and off the ferry is a somewhat vexing but nothing that is unmanageable. The Clipper folks ought to figure out how to expand the seating in the waiting rooms, that would help.

review.name: Bring Carry-on!
review.reviewBody:
Here are two tips:  1) if you can, travel with carry-on.  First, you'll save $10 (they charge for each checked bag) but you'll also save 50-60 minutes getting off the clipper on each end.   Carry-on passengers get off first, then passengers with checked luggage get off but only AFTER all the luggage, one s-l-o-w m-o-t-i-o-n crain lift at a time, is off the clipper.   And, you get the pleasure of watching this process while standing dockside.   I'm always wary of companies with less than efficient processes claim that "Government regulations require that..." 

2) Bring food.  We have to eat Gluten Free, and they have limited options on the ship.   When you are departing at 7:30 in the morning, the family can get hangry.   

Why only 4 stars?...the service is overpriced:  US$830 (plus $40 in checked baggage fees RT, so $870) for a family of 5 RT.  Victoria is worth it, but next time I will drive from Seattle.  The car ferry from Port Angeles, WA to Victoria would have been $305 RT for all of us and our car.  And with the checked-baggage "Gov't regulated" waiting...we would have arrived to our hotel sooner vs the Clipper.  You are now trip-advised.

review.name: Summer 2018 Experience & tips for future travelers
review.reviewBody:
The overall experience for our 2 day 1 night stay was about what I expected.  Some things that happen can be unavoidable and always expect the unexpected.  Here is a couple things to note for others looking into this (& Victoria Clipper as a suggested opportunity to improve).
The city tour (bus) we were ‘told’ to board was not a double-Decker as they/you advertised on your website.  When I asked to board another double-Decker bus parked there I was told no.  Also, the driver’s attempt to be a comedienne could have been interpreted as offensive to some.  Turn up the fans on the hot days, the buses are warm!
Our Butterfly Garden tour was limited to 40 minutes, which made us feel rushed because we were threatened to be left there if we did not get back on the same bus with the same driver in the allotted time.  If it is crowded it will take at least this much time to enjoy all of it.  We would have liked a bit more time to enjoy it longer.  No food options here, snacks & soda vending machines.
Our Butchart Garden tickets were not given to us until we left the Butterfly Garden, sort of held for ransom to insure we got on the bus?  It would be nice to have some sort of alternative “proof I paid”, in the event something goes awry given the 3rd party contracted service this is.  Review the food options here first before going – pack & plan if you need to.
The waiting area to be boarded past customs (in Victoria) needs to be made more comfortable – maybe consider air conditioning?  When the room is packed full of people and it is a warm day outside, those tin chairs and 3 fans running just don’t cut it.  We waited nearly an hour in this pleasantry.  
Also when there is an arrival/departure delay your employees should inform passengers of this BEFORE they pass through the customs area.  Certainly waiting outside on the grass, maybe under some shade would be more comfortable, especially for the elderly and those with young children.   

Bottom line is delays can be understood, if care for your comfort is taken into consideration.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Craft Cocktail and Mocktail Tours

name: Seattle Craft Cocktail and Mocktail Tours
description: Sip Seattle’s finest craft cocktails and mocktails on this exclusive food and drink tour where you’ll be granted premium access to both renowned establishments and hidden speakeasies. Enjoy expertly crafted drinks paired with thoughtfully curated bites, making this the perfect all-inclusive night out. Every sip and bite tells the story, craftsmanship, and artistry of the founders and the creative minds who brought them to life. This tour is about connecting with the heart of Belltown’s cocktail culture in an unforgettable way. Whether you’re discovering a famous bar in a new light or stepping into a hidden speakeasy for the first time, this experience offers an exclusive opportunity to explore the very best of Belltown’s cocktail, mocktail, and culinary scene.

itemListElement.name: Show Me Seattle On Foot Downtown Walking Tour

name: Show Me Seattle On Foot Downtown Walking Tour
description: Take in all the iconic sites of downtown Seattle and explore the rich culture of this vibrant city in this super entertaining two-hour walking tour. Real Seattle locals will guide you through the past and present to experience this dynamic urban center that attracts visitors from around the globe. You’ll visit the Seattle Spheres and the Amazon campus, ride the historic monorail, and enjoy an intimate visit to Pike Place Market. See the Space Needle, Chihuly Gardens, MoPOP, Climate Pledge Arena, T-Mobile Park, Lumen Field, The Seattle Art Museum, The Harbor Steps, Post Alley, Victor Steinbruck Park, SAM, Benaroya and the brand-new Overlook Park and waterfront. The best and most comprehensive walking tour in Seattle!
